&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Render terms cloud, hugo supports &lt;code&gt;tag&lt;/code&gt; and &lt;code&gt;category&lt;/code&gt; terms by default, if you want to add your custom terms. Follow the instructions in the &lt;a href="https://gohugo.io/content-management/taxonomies/#configure-taxonomies"&gt;document&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 class="header-anchor-wrapper"&gt;Usage
&lt;a href="#usage" class="header-anchor-link"&gt;
&lt;svg
xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg"
width="1rem" height="1rem" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none"
stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round"
stroke-linejoin="round"&gt;
&lt;line x1="4" y1="9" x2="20" y2="9"&gt;&lt;/line&gt;&lt;line x1="4" y1="15" x2="20" y2="15"&gt;&lt;/line&gt;&lt;line x1="10" y1="3" x2="8" y2="21"&gt;&lt;/line&gt;&lt;line x1="16" y1="3" x2="14" y2="21"&gt;&lt;/line&gt;
&lt;/svg&gt;
&lt;/a&gt;
&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;pre&gt;&lt;code&gt;{{&amp;lt; terms-cloud terms=&amp;quot;&amp;quot; sortby=&amp;quot;&amp;quot; order=&amp;quot;&amp;quot; /&amp;gt;}}
